{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"I just want to share with you"},{"time":2360,"text":"what I have been experiencing\nover the last five years"},{"time":4960,"text":"in having the great privilege of traveling"},{"time":7280,"text":"to many of the poorest\ncountries in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9520,"text":"This scene is one\nI see all the time everywhere,"},{"time":13440,"text":"and these young children\nare looking at a smartphone,"},{"time":16600,"text":"and the smartphone is having a huge impact\nin even the poorest countries."},{"time":21120,"text":"I said to my team, you know,"},{"time":22760,"text":"what I see is a rise in aspirations\nall over the world."},{"time":26520,"text":"In fact, it seems to me\nthat there's a convergence of aspirations."},{"time":30720,"text":"And I asked a team of economists\nto actually look into this."},{"time":34360,"text":"Is this true?"},{"time":35600,"text":"Are aspirations converging\nall around the world?"},{"time":38440,"text":"So they looked at things like Gallup polls\nabout satisfaction in life"},{"time":42720,"text":"and what they learned was\nthat if you have access to the internet,"},{"time":47200,"text":"your satisfaction goes up."},{"time":49320,"text":"But another thing happens\nthat's very important:"},{"time":52200,"text":"your reference income,"},{"time":54120,"text":"the income to which you compare your own,"},{"time":56800,"text":"also goes up."},{"time":58280,"text":"Now, if the reference income\nof a nation, for example,"},{"time":61720,"text":"goes up 10 percent"},{"time":63120,"text":"by comparing themselves to the outside,"},{"time":65360,"text":"then on average,"},{"time":67640,"text":"people's own incomes\nhave to go up at least five percent"},{"time":70720,"text":"to maintain the same\nlevel of satisfaction."},{"time":73280,"text":"But when you get down\ninto the lower percentiles of income,"},{"time":77280,"text":"your income has to go up much more"},{"time":79520,"text":"if the reference income\ngoes up 10 percent,"},{"time":81600,"text":"something like 20 percent."},{"time":83200,"text":"And so with this rise of aspirations,"},{"time":85720,"text":"the fundamental question is:"},{"time":87560,"text":"Are we going to have a situation"},{"time":89160,"text":"where aspirations\nare linked to opportunity"},{"time":92360,"text":"and you get dynamism and economic growth,"},{"time":95120,"text":"like that which happened\nin the country I was born in, in Korea?"},{"time":98880,"text":"Or are aspirations\ngoing to meet frustration?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":103920,"text":"This is a real concern,\nbecause between 2012 and 2015,"},{"time":108400,"text":"terrorism incidents\nincreased by 74 percent."},{"time":111360,"text":"The number of deaths from terrorism\nwent up 150 percent."},{"time":115640,"text":"Right now, two billion people"},{"time":117520,"text":"live in conditions\nof fragility, conflict, violence,"},{"time":120120,"text":"and by 2030, more than 60 percent\nof the world's poor"},{"time":125600,"text":"will live in these situations\nof fragility, conflict and violence."},{"time":129560,"text":"And so what do we do\nabout meeting these aspirations?"},{"time":132520,"text":"Are there new ways of thinking"},{"time":134240,"text":"about how we can rise\nto meet these aspirations?"},{"time":137280,"text":"Because if we don't,\nI'm extremely worried."},{"time":140320,"text":"Aspirations are rising as never before\nbecause of access to the internet."},{"time":144680,"text":"Everyone knows how everyone else lives."},{"time":147200,"text":"Has our ability to meet those aspirations"},{"time":150120,"text":"risen as well?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151560,"text":"And just to get at the details of this,"},{"time":153520,"text":"I want to share with you\nmy own personal story."},{"time":155960,"text":"This is not my mother,"},{"time":158000,"text":"but during the Korean War,"},{"time":159720,"text":"my mother literally took her own sister,"},{"time":162200,"text":"her younger sister, on her back,"},{"time":164120,"text":"and walked at least part of the way"},{"time":166560,"text":"to escape Seoul during the Korean War."},{"time":170280,"text":"Now, through a series of miracles,"},{"time":173200,"text":"my mother and father both got\nscholarships to go to New York City."},{"time":177320,"text":"They actually met in New York City\nand got married in New York City."},{"time":181960,"text":"My father, too, was a refugee."},{"time":184200,"text":"At the age of 19, he left his family\nin the northern part of the country,"},{"time":188600,"text":"escaped through the border"},{"time":190280,"text":"and never saw his family again."},{"time":192640,"text":"Now, when they were married\nand living in New York,"},{"time":195800,"text":"my father was a waiter\nat Patricia Murphy's restaurant."},{"time":198760,"text":"Their aspirations went up."},{"time":200920,"text":"They understood what it was like\nto live in a place like New York City"},{"time":204880,"text":"in the 1950s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206760,"text":"Well, my brother was born\nand they came back to Korea,"},{"time":210840,"text":"and we had what I remember\nas kind of an idyllic life,"},{"time":214880,"text":"but what was happening\nin Korea at that time"},{"time":217360,"text":"was the country was one\nof the poorest in the world"},{"time":220560,"text":"and there was political upheaval."},{"time":222200,"text":"There were demonstrations just down\nthe street from our house all the time,"},{"time":225760,"text":"students protesting\nagainst the military government."},{"time":230640,"text":"And at the time,"},{"time":232680,"text":"the aspirations of the World Bank Group,\nthe organization I lead now,"},{"time":236160,"text":"were extremely low for Korea."},{"time":239040,"text":"Their idea was that Korea would\nfind it difficult without foreign aid"},{"time":243080,"text":"to provide its people with more\nthan the bare necessities of life."},{"time":247440,"text":"So the situation is\nKorea is in a tough position,"},{"time":250960,"text":"my parents have seen\nwhat life is like in the United States."},{"time":253840,"text":"They got married there.\nMy brother was born there."},{"time":256240,"text":"And they felt that in order\nto give us an opportunity"},{"time":259600,"text":"to reach their aspirations for us,"},{"time":262200,"text":"we had to go and come back\nto the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264560,"text":"Now, we came back."},{"time":266880,"text":"First we went to Dallas."},{"time":268160,"text":"My father did his dental degree\nall over again."},{"time":270880,"text":"And then we ended up\nmoving to Iowa, of all places."},{"time":274200,"text":"We grew up in Iowa."},{"time":275960,"text":"And in Iowa, we went\nthrough the whole course."},{"time":278360,"text":"I went to high school, I went to college."},{"time":280840,"text":"And then one day,\nsomething that I'll never forget,"},{"time":285920,"text":"my father picked me up\nafter my sophomore year in college,"},{"time":290680,"text":"and he was driving me home,"},{"time":292040,"text":"and he said, \"Jim,\nwhat are your aspirations?"},{"time":294200,"text":"What do you want to study?\nWhat do you want to do?\""},{"time":296640,"text":"And I said, \"Dad,\" --"},{"time":297880,"text":"My mother actually was a philosopher,\nand had filled us with ideas"},{"time":301160,"text":"about protest and social justice,"},{"time":303520,"text":"and I said, \"Dad, I'm going to study\npolitical science and philosophy,"},{"time":307200,"text":"and I'm going to become\npart of a political movement.\""},{"time":310320,"text":"My father, the Korean dentist,"},{"time":312000,"text":"slowly pulled the car\nover to the side of the road --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":316200,"text":"He looked back at me, and he said,"},{"time":317920,"text":"\"Jim, you finish your medical residency,\nyou can study anything you want.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":321421,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":323000,"text":"Now, I've told this story\nto a mostly Asian audience before."},{"time":327960,"text":"Nobody laughs. They just shake their head."},{"time":330520,"text":"Of course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335200,"text":"So, tragically,\nmy father died at a young age,"},{"time":340240,"text":"30 years ago at the age of 57,"},{"time":342720,"text":"what happens to be how old I am right now,"},{"time":345240,"text":"and when he died in the middle\nof my medical and graduate studies --"},{"time":348480,"text":"You see, I actually got around it\nby doing medicine and anthropology."},{"time":351920,"text":"I studied both of them in graduate school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356880,"text":"But then right about that time,\nI met these two people,"},{"time":359840,"text":"Ophelia Dahl and Paul Farmer."},{"time":361960,"text":"And Paul and I were in the same program."},{"time":364000,"text":"We were studying medicine"},{"time":365600,"text":"and at the same time\ngetting our PhD's in anthropology."},{"time":368360,"text":"And we began to ask\nsome pretty fundamental questions."},{"time":371200,"text":"For people who have the great privilege\nof studying medicine and anthropology --"},{"time":376120,"text":"I had come from parents who were refugees."},{"time":378280,"text":"Paul grew up literally\nin a bus in a swamp in Florida."},{"time":382760,"text":"He liked to call himself \"white trash.\""},{"time":385360,"text":"And so we had this opportunity"},{"time":388280,"text":"and we said,"},{"time":389520,"text":"what is it that we need to do?"},{"time":391000,"text":"Given our ridiculously\nelaborate educations,"},{"time":393760,"text":"what is the nature\nof our responsibility to the world?"},{"time":397120,"text":"And we decided that we needed\nto start an organization."},{"time":400400,"text":"It's called Partners in Health."},{"time":401920,"text":"And by the way,\nthere's a movie made about that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407080,"text":"There's a movie\nthat was just a brilliant movie"},{"time":409320,"text":"they made about it\ncalled \"Bending the Arc.\""},{"time":411440,"text":"It launched at Sundance this past January."},{"time":413880,"text":"Jeff Skoll is here."},{"time":415120,"text":"Jeff is one of the ones\nwho made it happen."},{"time":418080,"text":"And we began to think\nabout what it would take for us"},{"time":422920,"text":"to actually have our aspirations\nreach the level"},{"time":426520,"text":"of some of the poorest\ncommunities in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428800,"text":"This is my very first visit\nto Haiti in 1988,"},{"time":432000,"text":"and in 1988, we elaborated\na sort of mission statement,"},{"time":437360,"text":"which is we are going to make\na preferential option for the poor"},{"time":441240,"text":"in health."},{"time":442480,"text":"Now, it took us a long time, and we\nwere graduate students in anthropology."},{"time":446040,"text":"We were reading up one side of Marx\nand down the other."},{"time":448680,"text":"Habermas. Fernand Braudel."},{"time":451160,"text":"We were reading everything"},{"time":452840,"text":"and we had to come to a conclusion\nof how are we going to structure our work?"},{"time":456920,"text":"So \"O for the P,\" we called it,"},{"time":458800,"text":"a preferential option for the poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461560,"text":"The most important thing\nabout a preferential option for the poor"},{"time":464640,"text":"is what it's not."},{"time":466360,"text":"It's not a preferential option\nfor your own sense of heroism."},{"time":470640,"text":"It's not a preferential option"},{"time":472120,"text":"for your own idea about\nhow to lift the poor out of poverty."},{"time":475720,"text":"It's not a preferential option\nfor your own organization."},{"time":478640,"text":"And the hardest of all,"},{"time":480560,"text":"it's not a preferential option\nfor your poor."},{"time":483840,"text":"It's a preferential option for the poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486440,"text":"So what do you do?"},{"time":487880,"text":"Well, Haiti, we started building --"},{"time":491760,"text":"Everyone told us, the cost-effective thing"},{"time":494040,"text":"is just focus on vaccination\nand maybe a feeding program."},{"time":497200,"text":"But what the Haitians wanted\nwas a hospital."},{"time":501000,"text":"They wanted schools."},{"time":502280,"text":"They wanted to provide their children\nwith the opportunities"},{"time":505160,"text":"that they'd been hearing about\nfrom others, relatives, for example,"},{"time":509200,"text":"who had gone to the United States."},{"time":511120,"text":"They wanted the same kinds\nof opportunities as my parents did."},{"time":516159,"text":"I recognized them."},{"time":518159,"text":"And so that's what we did.\nWe built hospitals."},{"time":520360,"text":"We provided education."},{"time":522200,"text":"And we did everything we could\nto try to give them opportunities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525640,"text":"Now, my experience really became intense"},{"time":528320,"text":"at Partners in Health\nin this community, Carabayllo,"},{"time":531600,"text":"in the northern slums of Lima, Peru."},{"time":536200,"text":"And in this community,"},{"time":537440,"text":"we started out by really just going\nto people's homes and talking to people,"},{"time":541080,"text":"and we discovered an outbreak, an epidemic\nof multidrug-resistant tuberculosis."},{"time":546360,"text":"This is Melquiades."},{"time":547640,"text":"Melquiades was a patient at that time,\nhe was about 18 years old,"},{"time":552480,"text":"and he had a very difficult form\nof drug-resistant tuberculosis."},{"time":557280,"text":"All of the gurus in the world,\nthe global health gurus,"},{"time":560080,"text":"said it is not cost-effective\nto treat drug-resistant tuberculosis."},{"time":564920,"text":"It's too complicated. It's too expensive."},{"time":566897,"text":"You just can't do it. It can't be done."},{"time":569760,"text":"And in addition,\nthey were getting angry at us,"},{"time":572960,"text":"because the implication was"},{"time":574520,"text":"if it could be done,\nwe would have done it."},{"time":576920,"text":"Who do you think you are?"},{"time":578640,"text":"And the people that we fought with\nwere the World Health Organization"},{"time":581920,"text":"and probably the organization\nwe fought with most"},{"time":585080,"text":"was the World Bank Group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586640,"text":"Now, we did everything we could"},{"time":590880,"text":"to convince Melquiades\nto take his medicines,"},{"time":593320,"text":"because it's really hard,"},{"time":594840,"text":"and not once during the time of treatment\ndid Melquiades's family ever say,"},{"time":598720,"text":"\"Hey, you know, Melquiades\nis just not cost-effective."},{"time":601960,"text":"Why don't you go on\nand treat somebody else?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":604120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605440,"text":"I hadn't seen Melquiades\nfor about 10 years"},{"time":607720,"text":"and when we had\nour annual meetings in Lima, Peru"},{"time":610840,"text":"a couple of years ago,"},{"time":612400,"text":"the filmmakers found him"},{"time":614640,"text":"and here is us getting together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616600,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":623560,"text":"He has become a bit of a media star\nbecause he goes to the film openings,"},{"time":627080,"text":"and he knows how to work an audience now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":631280,"text":"But as soon as we won --"},{"time":633440,"text":"We did win. We won the argument."},{"time":635280,"text":"You should treat\nmultidrug-resistant tuberculosis --"},{"time":638160,"text":"we heard the same arguments\nin the early 2000s about HIV."},{"time":642120,"text":"All of the leading global health\npeople in the world said"},{"time":645040,"text":"it is impossible\nto treat HIV in poor countries."},{"time":648320,"text":"Too expensive, too complicated,\nyou can't do it."},{"time":650800,"text":"Compared to drug-resistant TB treatment,"},{"time":652760,"text":"it's actually easier."},{"time":654720,"text":"And we were seeing patients like this."},{"time":657680,"text":"Joseph Jeune."},{"time":658920,"text":"Joseph Jeune also never mentioned\nthat he was not cost-effective."},{"time":662360,"text":"A few months of medicines,\nand this is what he looked like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":667640,"text":"We call that the Lazarus Effect\nof HIV treatment."},{"time":670160,"text":"Joseline came to us looking like this."},{"time":672480,"text":"This is what she looked like\na few months later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":674760,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":677480,"text":"Now, our argument, our battle, we thought,"},{"time":681080,"text":"was with the organizations\nthat kept saying it's not cost-effective."},{"time":685080,"text":"We were saying, no,"},{"time":686520,"text":"preferential option for the poor\nrequires us to raise our aspirations"},{"time":690440,"text":"to meet those of the poor for themselves."},{"time":692417,"text":"And they said, well, that's a nice thought\nbut it's just not cost-effective."},{"time":696080,"text":"So in the nerdy way\nthat we have operated Partners in Health,"},{"time":702640,"text":"we wrote a book against,\nbasically, the World Bank."},{"time":705360,"text":"It says that because the World Bank"},{"time":708000,"text":"has focused so much\non just economic growth"},{"time":711880,"text":"and said that governments\nhave to shrink their budgets"},{"time":715680,"text":"and reduce expenditures\nin health, education and social welfare --"},{"time":719760,"text":"we thought that was fundamentally wrong."},{"time":721760,"text":"And we argued with the World Bank."},{"time":723640,"text":"And then a crazy thing happened."},{"time":725960,"text":"President Obama nominated me\nto be President of the World Bank."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":734960,"text":"Now, when I went to do the vetting process\nwith President Obama's team,"},{"time":739800,"text":"they had a copy of \"Dying For Growth,\"\nand they had read every page."},{"time":743320,"text":"And I said, \"OK, that's it, right?"},{"time":745080,"text":"You guys are going to drop me?\""},{"time":746640,"text":"He goes, \"Oh, no, no, it's OK.\""},{"time":749080,"text":"And I was nominated,"},{"time":750480,"text":"and I walked through the door\nof the World Bank Group in July of 2012,"},{"time":755120,"text":"and that statement on the wall,\n\"Our dream is a world free of poverty.\""},{"time":758520,"text":"A few months after that,\nwe actually turned it into a goal:"},{"time":761520,"text":"end extreme poverty by 2030,"},{"time":764160,"text":"boost shared prosperity."},{"time":765440,"text":"That's what we do now\nat the World Bank Group."},{"time":767640,"text":"I feel like I have brought\nthe preferential option for the poor"},{"time":771640,"text":"to the World Bank Group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":773040,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":778480,"text":"But this is TED,"},{"time":779760,"text":"and so I want to share\nwith you some concerns,"},{"time":782360,"text":"and then make a proposal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785040,"text":"The Fourth Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":786680,"text":"now, you guys know\nso much better than I do,"},{"time":788800,"text":"but here's the thing that concerns me."},{"time":790680,"text":"What we hear about is job loss.\nYou've all heard that."},{"time":793240,"text":"Our own data suggest to us\nthat two thirds of all jobs,"},{"time":795880,"text":"currently existing jobs\nin developing countries,"},{"time":798143,"text":"will be lost because of automation."},{"time":799880,"text":"Now, you've got to make up for those jobs."},{"time":802040,"text":"Now, one of the ways\nto make up for those jobs"},{"time":804240,"text":"is to turn community health workers\ninto a formal labor force."},{"time":807920,"text":"That's what we want to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":809200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810480,"text":"We think the numbers will work out,"},{"time":812840,"text":"that as health outcomes get better\nand as people have formal work,"},{"time":816640,"text":"we're going to be able to train them"},{"time":818400,"text":"with the soft-skills training\nthat you add to it"},{"time":820680,"text":"to become workers\nthat will have a huge impact,"},{"time":824240,"text":"and that may be the one area\nthat grows the most."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827640,"text":"But here's the other thing\nthat bothers me:"},{"time":830240,"text":"right now it seems pretty clear to me\nthat the jobs of the future"},{"time":834160,"text":"will be more digitally demanding,"},{"time":836040,"text":"and there is a crisis\nin childhood stunting."},{"time":840000,"text":"So these are photos from Charles Nelson,\nwho shared these with us"},{"time":843600,"text":"from Harvard Medical School."},{"time":845080,"text":"And what these photos show\non the one side, on the left side,"},{"time":849880,"text":"is a three-month-old who has been stunted:"},{"time":854320,"text":"not adequate nutrition,\nnot adequate stimulation."},{"time":856880,"text":"And on the other side,\nof course, is a normal child,"},{"time":859480,"text":"and the normal child\nhas all of these neuronal connections."},{"time":862360,"text":"Now, the neuronal connections\nare important,"},{"time":864840,"text":"because that is\nthe definition of human capital."},{"time":868080,"text":"Now, we know that we\ncan reduce these rates."},{"time":871800,"text":"We can reduce these rates\nof childhood stunting quickly,"},{"time":875200,"text":"but if we don't, India, for example,\nwith 38 percent childhood stunting,"},{"time":879680,"text":"how are they going to compete\nin the economy of the future"},{"time":882440,"text":"if 40 percent of their future workers\ncannot achieve educationally"},{"time":888320,"text":"and certainly we worry\nabout achieving economically"},{"time":892080,"text":"in a way that will help\nthe country as a whole grow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895880,"text":"Now, what are we going to do?"},{"time":898520,"text":"78 trillion dollars\nis the size of the global economy."},{"time":902400,"text":"8.55 trillion dollars are sitting\nin negative interest rate bonds."},{"time":906320,"text":"That means that you give\nthe German central bank your money"},{"time":910800,"text":"and then you pay them to keep your money."},{"time":913320,"text":"That's a negative interest rate bond."},{"time":915160,"text":"24.4 trillion dollars\nin very low-earning government bonds."},{"time":918360,"text":"And 8 trillion literally sitting\nin the hands of rich people"},{"time":923600,"text":"under their very large mattresses."},{"time":926040,"text":"What we are trying to do\nis now use our own tools --"},{"time":930000,"text":"and just to get nerdy for a second,"},{"time":931720,"text":"we're talking about\nfirst-loss risk debt instruments,"},{"time":934240,"text":"we're talking about derisking,\nblended finance,"},{"time":936840,"text":"we're talking about\npolitical risk insurance,"},{"time":939360,"text":"credit enhancement --"},{"time":940600,"text":"all these things that I've now learned\nat the World Bank Group"},{"time":943560,"text":"that rich people use every single day\nto make themselves richer,"},{"time":947720,"text":"but we haven't used aggressively enough\non behalf of the poor"},{"time":951480,"text":"to bring this capital in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":953120,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":960280,"text":"So does this work?"},{"time":962440,"text":"Can you actually bring\nprivate-sector players into a country"},{"time":967280,"text":"and really make things work?"},{"time":968680,"text":"Well, we've done it a couple of times."},{"time":970560,"text":"This is Zambia, Scaling Solar."},{"time":972800,"text":"It's a box-set solution\nfrom the World Bank"},{"time":975000,"text":"where we come in\nand we do all the things you need"},{"time":977440,"text":"to attract private-sector investors."},{"time":979320,"text":"And in this case, Zambia went\nfrom having a cost of electricity"},{"time":983920,"text":"at 25 cents a kilowatt-hour,"},{"time":986440,"text":"and by just doing simple things,\ndoing the auction,"},{"time":990200,"text":"changing some policies,"},{"time":991720,"text":"we were able to bring the cost down."},{"time":994720,"text":"Lowest bid,"},{"time":995960,"text":"25 cents a kilowatt-hour for Zambia?"},{"time":998440,"text":"The lowest bid was 4.7 cents\na kilowatt-hour. It's possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1002640,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004800,"text":"But here's my proposal for you."},{"time":1006760,"text":"This is from a group called Zipline,"},{"time":1008680,"text":"a cool company, and they\nliterally are rocket scientists."},{"time":1011560,"text":"They figured out\nhow to use drones in Rwanda."},{"time":1014000,"text":"This is me launching a drone in Rwanda"},{"time":1016240,"text":"that delivers blood\nanywhere in the country"},{"time":1019200,"text":"in less than an hour."},{"time":1020760,"text":"So we save lives,"},{"time":1022240,"text":"this program saved lives --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024119,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1025160,"text":"This program made money for Zipline"},{"time":1026920,"text":"and this program saved\nhuge amounts of money for Rwanda."},{"time":1030960,"text":"That's what we need,\nand we need that from all of you."},{"time":1033680,"text":"I'm asking you, carve out\na little bit of time in your brains"},{"time":1036960,"text":"to think about the technology\nthat you work on,"},{"time":1039560,"text":"the companies that you start,\nthe design that you do."},{"time":1042200,"text":"Think a little bit and work with us"},{"time":1045160,"text":"to see if we can come up with these kinds\nof extraordinary win-win solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049480,"text":"I'm going to leave you\nwith one final story."},{"time":1052880,"text":"I was in Tanzania,\nand I was in a classroom."},{"time":1055200,"text":"This is me with a classroom\nof 11-year-olds."},{"time":1059480,"text":"And I asked them, as I always do,"},{"time":1061120,"text":"\"What do you want to be when you grow up?\""},{"time":1063200,"text":"Two raised their hands and said,"},{"time":1064960,"text":"\"I want to be President\nof the World Bank.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068840,"text":"And just like you, my own team\nand their teachers laughed."},{"time":1072280,"text":"But then I stopped them."},{"time":1073840,"text":"I said, \"Look, I want to tell you a story."},{"time":1077040,"text":"When I was born in South Korea,\nthis is what it looked like."},{"time":1081280,"text":"This is where I came from."},{"time":1083360,"text":"And when I was three years old,"},{"time":1086240,"text":"in preschool,"},{"time":1088320,"text":"I don't think that George David Woods,\nthe President of the World Bank,"},{"time":1091720,"text":"if he had visited Korea on that day\nand come to my classroom,"},{"time":1095320,"text":"that he would have thought"},{"time":1096680,"text":"that the future President\nof the World Bank"},{"time":1098720,"text":"was sitting in that classroom."},{"time":1100200,"text":"Don't let anyone ever tell you"},{"time":1102520,"text":"that you cannot be\nPresident of the World Bank.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105320,"text":"Now -- thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108160,"text":"Let me leave you with one thought."},{"time":1110240,"text":"I came from a country\nthat was the poorest in the world."},{"time":1112920,"text":"I'm President of the World Bank."},{"time":1114520,"text":"I cannot and I will not\npull up the ladder behind me."},{"time":1117720,"text":"This is urgent."},{"time":1119280,"text":"Aspirations are going up."},{"time":1120800,"text":"Everywhere aspirations are going up."},{"time":1123120,"text":"You folks in this room, work with us."},{"time":1125760,"text":"We know that we can find\nthose Zipline-type solutions"},{"time":1129800,"text":"and help the poor\nleapfrog into a better world,"},{"time":1133120,"text":"but it won't happen\nuntil we work together."},{"time":1136240,"text":"The future \"you\" --\nand especially for your children --"},{"time":1139000,"text":"the future you"},{"time":1140600,"text":"will depend on how much care\nand compassion we bring"},{"time":1143600,"text":"to ensuring that the future \"us\"\nprovides equality of opportunity"},{"time":1148240,"text":"for every child in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1149680,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1152680,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1155760,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1161040,"text":"Chris Anderson: You'd almost think"},{"time":1162720,"text":"people are surprised\nto hear a talk like this"},{"time":1164880,"text":"from the President of the World Bank."},{"time":1166720,"text":"It's kind of cool."},{"time":1167960,"text":"I'd encourage you to even be\na little more specific on your proposal."},{"time":1171240,"text":"There's many investors,\nentrepreneurs in this room."},{"time":1175760,"text":"How will you partner with them?\nWhat's your proposal?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1178280,"text":"Jim Yong Kim: Can I get nerdy\nfor just a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1180560,"text":"CA: Get nerdy. Absolutely.\nJYK: So here's what we did."},{"time":1183160,"text":"Insurance companies never invest\nin developing country infrastructure,"},{"time":1186480,"text":"for example, because\nthey can't take the risk."},{"time":1188680,"text":"They're holding money\nfor people who pay for insurance."},{"time":1191320,"text":"So what we did was a Swedish\nInternational Development Association"},{"time":1194480,"text":"gave us a little bit of money,"},{"time":1195960,"text":"we went out and raised a little bit\nmore money, a hundred million,"},{"time":1199120,"text":"and we took first loss,\nmeaning if this thing goes bad,"},{"time":1201760,"text":"10 percent of the loss we'll just eat,"},{"time":1203640,"text":"and the rest of you will be safe."},{"time":1205440,"text":"And that created\na 90-percent chunk, tranche"},{"time":1209200,"text":"that was triple B, investment-grade,\nso the insurance companies invested."},{"time":1212680,"text":"So for us, what we're doing\nis taking our public money"},{"time":1217320,"text":"and using it to derisk\nspecific instruments"},{"time":1220880,"text":"to bring people in from the outside."},{"time":1222640,"text":"So all of you who are sitting\non trillions of dollars of cash,"},{"time":1225600,"text":"come to us. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1226840,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1227880,"text":"CA: And what you're specifically\nlooking for are investment proposals"},{"time":1231160,"text":"that create employment\nin the developing world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1233400,"text":"JYK: Absolutely. Absolutely."},{"time":1234800,"text":"So these will be, for example,\nin infrastructure that brings energy,"},{"time":1238560,"text":"builds roads, bridges, ports."},{"time":1241040,"text":"These kinds of things\nare necessary to create jobs,"},{"time":1243800,"text":"but also what we're saying is"},{"time":1246120,"text":"you may think that the technology\nyou're working on"},{"time":1248560,"text":"or the business that you're working on"},{"time":1250440,"text":"may not have applications\nin the developing world,"},{"time":1253520,"text":"but look at Zipline."},{"time":1254880,"text":"And that Zipline thing didn't happen"},{"time":1256920,"text":"just because of the quality\nof the technology."},{"time":1259120,"text":"It was because they engaged\nwith the Rwandans early"},{"time":1262320,"text":"and used artificial intelligence --"},{"time":1264200,"text":"one thing, Rwanda has great broadband --"},{"time":1267080,"text":"but these things fly\ncompletely on their own."},{"time":1269960,"text":"So we will help you do that.\nWe will make the introductions."},{"time":1272840,"text":"We will even provide financing.\nWe will help you do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1275560,"text":"CA: How much capital\nis the World Bank willing to deploy"},{"time":1278240,"text":"to back those kinds of efforts?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1279800,"text":"JYK: Chris, you're always getting me\nto try to do something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1283120,"text":"CA: I'm trying to get you in trouble.\nJYK: So here's what we're going to do."},{"time":1286720,"text":"We have 25 billion a year\nthat we're investing in poor countries,"},{"time":1291480,"text":"the poorest countries."},{"time":1292720,"text":"And as we invest\nover the next three years,"},{"time":1294800,"text":"25 billion a year,"},{"time":1296240,"text":"we have got to think with you"},{"time":1298120,"text":"about how to use that money\nmore effectively."},{"time":1300280,"text":"So I can't give you a specific number.\nIt depends on the quality of the ideas."},{"time":1304120,"text":"So bring us your ideas,"},{"time":1305680,"text":"and I don't think that financing\nis going to be the problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1311400,"text":"CA: All right, you heard it\nfrom the man himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313760,"text":"Jim, thanks so much.\nJYK: Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1316000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}